reading to your state or district, visit mz.com linked in the description below and

142
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,760
sign up for our mailing list.

143
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:49,599
That's I-M-S-E dot com.

144
00:09:49,599 --> 00:09:54,000
Additionally, check out Emily Hanford's groundbreaking podcast about what happened

145
00:09:54,000 --> 00:10:00,479
to literacy in the U.S. or click on one of the New York Times articles, all linked below.

146
00:10:00,479 --> 00:10:06,719
At MZ, we believe all students can learn, and all teachers can learn to teach them.

147
00:10:07,119 --> 00:10:13,400
Together, we can solve the U.S. literacy crisis, ensuring that all children everywhere are

148
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:20,039
given equitable access to the code to unlock literacy, opening doors to opportunities for

149
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:21,599
the rest of their lives.


